translation.src: her walrus that has slept hasn't applauded the peacock above my orangutans .
translation.tgt: hasn't her walrus that has slept applauded the peacock above my orangutans ?

translation.src: my tyrannosaurus who some peacock has admired hasn't changed .
translation.tgt: hasn't my tyrannosaurus who some peacock has admired changed ?

translation.src: our newts that haven't comforted our newt have smiled .
translation.tgt: have our newts that haven't comforted our newt smiled ?

translation.src: your unicorns who haven't moved have swum .
translation.tgt: have your unicorns who haven't moved swum ?

translation.src: some orangutans that haven't annoyed some yak have smiled .
translation.tgt: have some orangutans that haven't annoyed some yak smiled ?

translation.src: her unicorn that has amused our peacock hasn't amused my quail by my tyrannosaurus .
translation.tgt: hasn't her unicorn that has amused our peacock amused my quail by my tyrannosaurus ?

translation.src: some raven who hasn't changed has accepted our ravens with some xylophone .
translation.tgt: has some raven who hasn't changed accepted our ravens with some xylophone ?

translation.src: the walrus who has swum hasn't read .
translation.tgt: hasn't the walrus who has swum read ?

translation.src: my peacock that hasn't changed has waited .
translation.tgt: has my peacock that hasn't changed waited ?

translation.src: your vultures that have read haven't swum .
translation.tgt: haven't your vultures that have read swum ?

translation.src: our tyrannosaurus that has applauded our peacocks hasn't smiled .
translation.tgt: hasn't our tyrannosaurus that has applauded our peacocks smiled ?
